As for why guilds split apart when they don't seem to be able to handle planes or dragons without the CoG, quite honestly, I see that problem with the KGC, not the CoG.  The KGC enforces that people don't have the chance to go to the planes or dragons too often and in effect forces people to either band into large guilds or alliances that are exclusive and don't overlap in membership. So people leave to either join those guilds or alliances.  Relying on the CoG for that responsibility is not really fair in my opinion because that's not what the CoG is for. <p><HR>
