<br>
If you'd been paying attention to the CoG for the last year, if you've read any of the meeting logs, or read up, you would see that I've been trying to hand people a pole, as you say, all along. <br>
<br>
I've have ALWAYS said that the CoG is only as strong as the members who wish to do things for others OUTSIDE their guild, their alliance, or the CoG. If you want to learn how to fish (or kill a dragon), you can go on a CoG raid. If you want the CoG to hand you the fish every time (i.e. killing a dragon), you're in the wrong place. For months now, I've been talking up the idea of smaller guilds forming alliances to do their OWN plane and dragon raids. I've preached this over and over. In one case, I've actually tried to put 3 guilds together in email, just to get them to meet and consider it. The CoG planes and dragon raids are not and should not be considered the only way for you to get to the planes. But in order to do planes by yourselves as a small guild, you will either need very high levels (about 18 or so above 50's), or you will need numbers - which means an alliance. Yes, doing things like you've mentioned does strenghten your own guild. But doing those same things AND opening them up to the whole server not only strengthens your guild, it strenghtens the people who run the event, and if puts your guild's name out there as one who is open, friendly, and wants to do things for other guilds. I can tell you now... the Silver Daggers did not get to be a guild of almost 100 strong quality people by just doing things for itself. We did many CoG events, we got our name out their on everyone's lips and we built up alliances based on friendship. Now we are in an alliance with 3 other guilds, total membership well over 200 people, and are doing the planes and dragons on our own. <br>
<br>
As for your guild being pawns of the CoG, you need to stop looking at the CoG as some massive conspiracy to control the server. Almost everything that has gone on with the CoG has happened in a public forum, or in public meetings with logs posted afterwards. Your guild should be the one using the CoG... it is a tool. <br>
<br>
